@startuml
title Manage Users & Roles - Sequence Design
autonumber
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Admin" as Admin
participant "Web SPA" as Web
participant "api-gateway" as Gateway
participant "auth-service\nUsersController" as Users
participant "AuthService" as AuthService
database "auth.users" as DB
participant "AuthAuditLogger" as Audit

Admin -> Web: Search user and edit roles/enabled flag
Web -> Gateway: PATCH /api/v1/users/{id}/roles
Gateway -> Users: route with ADMIN JWT
Users -> AuthService: assignRoles(userId, roles, actor)
AuthService -> DB: load and update user roles
AuthService -> Audit: record role change
Users --> Web: UserResponse

Admin -> Web: Disable/enable user
Web -> Gateway: PATCH /api/v1/users/{id}/status
Gateway -> Users: route
Users -> AuthService: changeStatus(userId, enabled)
AuthService -> DB: update enabled flag
AuthService -> Audit: record account status change
Users --> Web: UserResponse
@enduml
